      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is really hard to figure out the exact severity of an injury without seeing a professional evaluation, so relying solely on home care carries risks. While RICE (rest, ice, compression, elevation) is helpful for minor sprains, severe swelling or inability to walk often indicate more serious damage that requires medical imaging like an X-ray to rule out fractures. I strongly recommend seeing a clinic or urgent care promptly to prevent long-term issues before you push too far on your own. It is always better to be safe and get a clear diagnosis now than to suffer complications later.",
