      "content": "You are likely justified in being cautious, as ignoring significant swelling and an inability to bear weight increases the risk of turning a simple sprain into a chronic stability issue. Even without a loud pop, stress fractures or severe ligament tears can sometimes present silently but still require proper diagnosis and treatment. Waiting until tomorrow is a risky gamble; if the pain persists or you can't manage without a crutch, seeing a doctor immediately is the safest and most effective choice for your recovery. Don't let the fear of a visit scare you away from getting clear answers now while you are still in the earliest stages of healing.",
