      "content": "That is actually not a solid plan because relying purely on the RICE method without a diagnosis can lead to worsening the injury if it is more severe than a simple bruise. Attempting to self-manage a significant ankle injury—even if it feels like a bruise—is risky, as untreated minor ligament tears or hairline fractures can lead to long-term instability and chronic pain. It is much safer to get a quick evaluation from a clinic to confirm the diagnosis and prevent future problems, which would ultimately save you more time and money in the long run. Please prioritize your recovery and seek professional medical advice rather than ignoring warning signs. I strongly encourage you to make that appointment soon for peace of mind and proper treatment.",
